window.__SCRIBE_DOC_SEARCH__ = [{"page":"index.html","title":"Overview","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"A practical map of the writing workspace, its current capabilities, and the fastest route into the codebase.","content":"ScribeAI developer documentation This directory describes the application as it works now. It is intended to get a developer from a fresh checkout to making safe changes without first reverse-engineering the UI, editor, and suggestion state machine. What this application is ScribeAI is a client-only React writing workspace. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - a mock, event-driven writing-partner feed; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions; - desktop workspace cards for keeping references over the editor; - responsive navigation and writing-partner panels. There is currently no backend, authentication, router, remote model call, document persistence, or file upload pipeline. Most navigation and document-management controls are presentation-only. The only persisted values are the two desktop column widths in browser localStorage. Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started and run the app and checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing agent, preview, pin, or document-context behavior. 4. Use UI and accessibility for respo"},{"page":"index.html#what-this-application-is","title":"What this application is","section":"Overview","excerpt":"ScribeAI is a client-only React writing workspace. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - a mock, event-driven writing-partner feed; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previe","content":"What this application is ScribeAI is a client-only React writing workspace. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - a mock, event-driven writing-partner feed; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions; - desktop workspace cards for keeping references over the editor;"},{"page":"index.html#fastest-route-into-the-codebase","title":"Fastest route into the codebase","section":"Overview","excerpt":"1. Follow Getting started and run the app and checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing agent, preview, pin, or document-context behavior","content":"Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started and run the app and checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing agent, preview, pin, or document-context behavior. 4. Use UI and accessibility for responsive layout, resizing, styling, and keyboard behavior."},{"page":"index.html#current-user-visible-behavior","title":"Current user-visible behavior","section":"Overview","excerpt":"","content":"Current user-visible behavior "},{"page":"index.html#repository-map","title":"Repository map","section":"Overview","excerpt":". ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Composition root and cross-feature orchestration │ ├── main.tsx React browser entry point │ ├── index.css Tailwind theme, layout rules, and editor overrides │ ├─","content":"Repository map . ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Composition root and cross-feature orchestration │ ├── main.tsx React browser entry point │ ├── index.css Tailwind theme, layout rules, and editor overrides │ ├── components/ UI components and component tests"},{"page":"index.html#terms-used-in-the-code","title":"Terms used in the code","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- Accepted document : all editor blocks except temporary suggestionPreview blocks. This is the content exposed to the agent context source. - Suggestion feed : the service-shaped interface that emits suggestion and agent","content":"Terms used in the code - Accepted document : all editor blocks except temporary suggestionPreview blocks. This is the content exposed to the agent context source. - Suggestion feed : the service-shaped interface that emits suggestion and agent-status events and accepts user steering."},{"page":"index.html#important-implementation-constraints","title":"Important implementation constraints","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- App.tsx is the composition root. It intentionally connects editor state, agent context, inbox state, previews, panel state, and workspace pins. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion lifecycle rules. UI c","content":"Important implementation constraints - App.tsx is the composition root. It intentionally connects editor state, agent context, inbox state, previews, panel state, and workspace pins. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion lifecycle rules. UI components dispatch intent; they should not recreate those rules locally."},{"page":"getting-started.html","title":"Getting started","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Install, run, inspect, and troubleshoot the project from a clean checkout.","content":"Getting started Prerequisites - Node.js ^20.19.0 or =22.12.0. This is the engine range required by the installed Vite 8 release. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. - A modern browser with ES2022, dynamic imports, media queries, pointer events, and ResizeObserver support. No environment variables, service credentials, database, or local backend are required. Install and run From the repository root: Open the local URL printed by Vite. Vite normally uses http://localhost:5173, but it will select another port if that one is occupied. Use npm ci, rather than npm install, for a clean checkout or CI job so dependency versions remain aligned with the lockfile. What to expect after startup The root URL opens the writing workspace with seeded document content and an empty suggestion inbox. Suggestions are injected manually from a temporary controller: 1. Keep the writing workspace open in one tab, or use the controller's Open writing workspace link. 2. Open /mock-suggestions on the same origin in a second tab, for example http://localhost:5173/mock-suggestions. 3. Choose one of the six suggestion kinds, complete its common and kind-specific fields, and send it. 4. The suggestion "},{"page":"getting-started.html#prerequisites","title":"Prerequisites","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"- Node.js ^20.19.0 or =22.12.0. This is the engine range required by the installed Vite 8 release. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. - A modern browser with ES2022, dynamic imports, media queries, pointer eve","content":"Prerequisites - Node.js ^20.19.0 or =22.12.0. This is the engine range required by the installed Vite 8 release. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. - A modern browser with ES2022, dynamic imports, media queries, pointer events, and ResizeObserver support."},{"page":"getting-started.html#install-and-run","title":"Install and run","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Open the local URL printed by Vite. Vite normally uses http://localhost:5173, but it will select another port if that one is occupied. Use npm ci, rather than npm install, for","content":"Install and run From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Open the local URL printed by Vite. Vite normally uses http://localhost:5173, but it will select another port if that one is occupied. Use npm ci, rather than npm install, for a clean checkout or CI job so dependency versions remain aligned with the lockfile."},{"page":"getting-started.html#what-to-expect-after-startup","title":"What to expect after startup","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The root URL opens the writing workspace with seeded document content and an empty suggestion inbox. Suggestions are injected manually from a temporary controller: 1. Keep the writing workspace open in one tab, or use th","content":"What to expect after startup The root URL opens the writing workspace with seeded document content and an empty suggestion inbox. Suggestions are injected manually from a temporary controller: 1. Keep the writing workspace open in one tab, or use the controller's Open writing workspace link."},{"page":"getting-started.html#developer-commands","title":"Developer commands","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some mini","content":"Developer commands A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some minified chunks exceed 500 kB. The main application bundle and parts of Mermaid are the principal contributors. This is a warning, not a failed build; treat a new error separately. The performance watch points in the Extension guide describe the relevant boundaries."},{"page":"getting-started.html#runtime-configuration","title":"Runtime configuration","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The application has no .env contract. Its current runtime inputs are hard-coded at the composition boundary: - initial editor content: initialContent; - research artifacts: artifacts; - temporary suggestion controller an","content":"Runtime configuration The application has no .env contract. Its current runtime inputs are hard-coded at the composition boundary: - initial editor content: initialContent; - research artifacts: artifacts; - temporary suggestion controller and channel: src/dev/mockSuggestions;"},{"page":"getting-started.html#browser-storage","title":"Browser storage","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the ","content":"Browser storage The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the current session. To reset the prototype completely, reload the page and remove those two keys from browser storage. All other application state is already in memory only."},{"page":"getting-started.html#first-pass-manual-tour","title":"First-pass manual tour","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from /mock-suggestions. 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and accept it; it be","content":"First-pass manual tour At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from /mock-suggestions. 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and accept it; it becomes a normal paragraph and the suggestion disappears."},{"page":"getting-started.html#common-problems","title":"Common problems","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"","content":"Common problems "},{"page":"getting-started.html#vite-refuses-to-start","title":"Vite refuses to start","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer.","content":"Vite refuses to start Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer."},{"page":"getting-started.html#fonts-look-different","title":"Fonts look different","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected.","content":"Fonts look different index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-mind-map-says-diagram-unavailable","title":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable”","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion.","content":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable” Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-workspace-pin-is-missing","title":"A workspace pin is missing","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner befo","content":"A workspace pin is missing Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner before “Place on workspace” is available."},{"page":"getting-started.html#suggestion-behavior-seems-duplicated-in-development","title":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check that a new feed or context source is not being created on every render. App.tsx memoizes both. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React Strict","content":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development Check that a new feed or context source is not being created on every render. App.tsx memoizes both. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React StrictMode will exercise that path."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-manually-sent-suggestion-does-not-appear","title":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Confirm both tabs use exactly the same scheme, host, and port, and that the writing workspace was already open when Send was pressed. BroadcastChannel delivery is live-only. The controller reports an explicit error if th","content":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear Confirm both tabs use exactly the same scheme, host, and port, and that the writing workspace was already open when Send was pressed. BroadcastChannel delivery is live-only. The controller reports an explicit error if the browser does not provide the API."},{"page":"architecture.html","title":"Architecture","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Understand the browser-only system boundary, state ownership, data direction, and module responsibilities.","content":"Architecture System boundary The application is browser-only React. The entry point has one temporary pathname switch for /mock-suggestions; there is no routing library or server boundary in the current repository. The service-shaped interfaces exist, but their current implementations are in-memory. This separation is the main seam for adding a real agent or persistence later. Composition root App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createAgentContextSource creates the mutable document/artifact context and is memoized for the component lifetime. 3. createMockSuggestionFeed creates the feed with the existing context-shaped constructor seam and is also memoized. 4. useSuggestionInbox subscribes to the feed and owns the suggestion lifecycle reducer. 5. App bridges editor changes into agent context, creates editor preview blocks, translates preview resolution events back into inbox actions, and controls responsive panels. Keeping feed and context creation stable is important. Recreating either during a render would reset context revisions, reopen the manual channel, and resubscribe the inbox. St"},{"page":"architecture.html#system-boundary","title":"System boundary","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The application is browser-only React. The entry point has one temporary pathname switch for /mock-suggestions; there is no routing library or server boundary in the current repository. flowchart LR User[User] Shell[App ","content":"System boundary The application is browser-only React. The entry point has one temporary pathname switch for /mock-suggestions; there is no routing library or server boundary in the current repository. flowchart LR User[User] Shell[App composition root] Editor[BlockNote editor]"},{"page":"architecture.html#composition-root","title":"Composition root","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createAgentContextSource creates the mutable document/artifact context and is memoized f","content":"Composition root App.tsx creates and connects long-lived objects: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. createAgentContextSource creates the mutable document/artifact context and is memoized for the component lifetime."},{"page":"architecture.html#state-ownership","title":"State ownership","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state.","content":"State ownership There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state."},{"page":"architecture.html#module-boundaries","title":"Module boundaries","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"","content":"Module boundaries "},{"page":"architecture.html#src-editor","title":"src/editor","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - documentContext.ts flattens editor blocks into the agent-facing text snapshot and removes preview blocks. - preview","content":"src/editor - schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - documentContext.ts flattens editor blocks into the agent-facing text snapshot and removes preview blocks. - previewEvents.ts is a small in-process event bridge from the custom block renderer back to App."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-suggestions","title":"src/suggestions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed/context interfaces. - contextSource.ts stores revisioned document context and artifact references. - mockSuggestionFeed.ts implements the feed contract over the temporary i","content":"src/suggestions - types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed/context interfaces. - contextSource.ts stores revisioned document context and artifact references. - mockSuggestionFeed.ts implements the feed contract over the temporary injected-event channel."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-components","title":"src/components","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx renders the inbox, pinned section, detail v","content":"src/components - EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx renders the inbox, pinned section, detail view, steering form, and errors."},{"page":"architecture.html#bootstrap-and-runtime-sequence","title":"Bootstrap and runtime sequence","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App participant Editor as BlockNote participant Context as AgentContextSource participant Controller as Mock controller tab participant Feed as SuggestionFeed part","content":"Bootstrap and runtime sequence sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App participant Editor as BlockNote participant Context as AgentContextSource participant Controller as Mock controller tab participant Feed as SuggestionFeed participant Inbox as useSuggestionInbox"},{"page":"architecture.html#data-direction-and-dependency-rules","title":"Data direction and dependency rules","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → App composition root Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in suggestions/types.","content":"Data direction and dependency rules The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → App composition root Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in suggestions/types.ts, not in UI components."},{"page":"architecture.html#styling-architecture","title":"Styling architecture","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base fo","content":"Styling architecture Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base focus and typography rules;"},{"page":"architecture.html#build-and-runtime-assumptions","title":"Build and runtime assumptions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Mermaid is a dynamic chunk because MermaidDiagram im","content":"Build and runtime assumptions - TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Mermaid is a dynamic chunk because MermaidDiagram imports it lazily. - Google Fonts are external runtime requests. Font failure degrades to local fallbacks."},{"page":"architecture.html#architectural-invariants","title":"Architectural invariants","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never over","content":"Architectural invariants Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never overwrite it. 3. Agent context contains accepted content only, never preview blocks."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html","title":"Editor & suggestions","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Trace agent context, feed events, inbox transitions, editable previews, and workspace pins end to end.","content":"Editor and suggestion system This is the core interaction model: the editor supplies accepted document context, the feed emits events, the inbox reducer turns those events and user actions into state, and text suggestions can temporarily enter the document as editable previews. Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts. Suggestion kinds Kind Type Extra data Can preview into document? Visual treatment --- --- --- --- --- snippet TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail fact TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail term TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail outline StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards layout StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards mindMap MindMapSuggestion Mermaid source and accessible description No Lazy-rendered Mermaid diagram Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels; - createdAt: ordering and queue-eviction input. An update uses id to replace an exist"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#domain-model","title":"Domain model","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts.","content":"Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#suggestion-kinds","title":"Suggestion kinds","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed prese","content":"Suggestion kinds Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels;"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#agent-context","title":"Agent context","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"createAgentContextSource owns two inputs: - the latest DocumentSnapshot; - immutable artifact references supplied at construction. A document snapshot is a revision plus a flat array of { id, type, text } blocks. updateD","content":"Agent context createAgentContextSource owns two inputs: - the latest DocumentSnapshot; - immutable artifact references supplied at construction. A document snapshot is a revision plus a flat array of { id, type, text } blocks. updateDocument JSON-fingerprints the array and publishes only when the flattened content changes. The revision begins at 0 and increments for every unique snapshot."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-contract","title":"Feed contract","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"SuggestionFeed has three operations: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; sendSteering(prompt: string): Promise ; retry(): Promise ; } The event channel supports: Th","content":"Feed contract SuggestionFeed has three operations: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; sendSteering(prompt: string): Promise ; retry(): Promise ; } The event channel supports: The current mock implementation in mockSuggestionFeed.ts:"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#inbox-state-machine","title":"Inbox state machine","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selected","content":"Inbox state machine inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selectedId item shown in detail view"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-event-behavior","title":"Feed-event behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"","content":"Feed-event behavior "},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#queue-limit","title":"Queue limit","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that gro","content":"Queue limit The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that group, the oldest createdAt value is evicted first."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#user-action-behavior","title":"User-action behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"- Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismi","content":"User-action behavior - Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismiss is disabled while that item has the active preview."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#editable-preview-lifecycle","title":"Editable preview lifecycle","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as Sugge","content":"Editable preview lifecycle Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as SuggestionDock participant App"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-insertion","title":"Preview insertion","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted bl","content":"Preview insertion App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted blocks. If that block no longer exists, it falls back to the final accepted top-level block. The preview is inserted immediately after that block with:"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-rendering-and-resolution","title":"Preview rendering and resolution","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom b","content":"Preview rendering and resolution schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom block with a normal paragraph carrying the edited inline content."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#concurrent-feed-changes","title":"Concurrent feed changes","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports ","content":"Concurrent feed changes The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports withdrawal and the preview remains resolvable. Cancelling a withdrawn preview removes the suggestion; accepting any preview removes it."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#pins-and-workspace-cards","title":"Pins and workspace cards","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox ","content":"Pins and workspace cards Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox -- [ ]: Dismiss / accepted preview / retraction"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#mermaid-rendering","title":"Mermaid rendering","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - t","content":"Mermaid rendering Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - the rendered SVG is injected into a role=\"img\" container with a combined title and accessible description;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html","title":"UI & accessibility","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Work confidently with responsive panels, editor layout, keyboard input, focus, and visual conventions.","content":"UI and accessibility Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region. Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Viewport Navigation Document Writing partner Workspace cards --- --- --- --- --- =96rem Default 280 px Fluid Default 360 px Visible Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade. Desktop panel open state and mobile drawer open state are intentionally separate. Crossing into desktop closes any open drawers. Collapsing a desktop panel does not imply that its mobile drawer is open, and vice versa. Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column. Limits Column Minimum Absolute maxim"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#page-regions","title":"Page regions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace kee","content":"Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-layout","title":"Responsive layout","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first ","content":"Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#desktop-column-resizing","title":"Desktop column resizing","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column.","content":"Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#limits","title":"Limits","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes.","content":"Limits When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#input-behavior","title":"Input behavior","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"- Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and remo","content":"Input behavior - Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and removes the stored value."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-drawers","title":"Responsive drawers","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift","content":"Responsive drawers ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift+Tab wrapping inside known focusable elements;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#header-controls","title":"Header controls","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in ","content":"Header controls DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in both the visual badge and accessible label. When the desktop partner is already open, the header suppresses its unread badge because the count is visible in the dock."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#editor-surface","title":"Editor surface","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - ex","content":"Editor surface DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - extra minimum canvas height when a workspace card extends beyond the document."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#suggestion-dock-interaction","title":"Suggestion dock interaction","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The writing partner has two mutually exclusive views: - queue view: steering form, error, Pins, and live inbox; - detail view: full suggestion, sources, visual content, and actions. Selecting an item marks it viewed and ","content":"Suggestion dock interaction The writing partner has two mutually exclusive views: - queue view: steering form, error, Pins, and live inbox; - detail view: full suggestion, sources, visual content, and actions. Selecting an item marks it viewed and scrolls the dock to the top. Unread live and pinned entries contribute to the count. Workspace cards do not."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#workspace-card-input-and-bounds","title":"Workspace card input and bounds","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted","content":"Workspace card input and bounds Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted with; - automatic clamping when canvas dimensions change;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#focus-and-semantics-checklist","title":"Focus and semantics checklist","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are","content":"Focus and semantics checklist When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are named modal dialogs and restore focus;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#styling-conventions","title":"Styling conventions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette","content":"Styling conventions Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette is declared as brand-50 through brand-900 in index.css. BlockNote has a parallel set of --bn- variables in the same file. When changing a core color, check both systems as well as hard-coded neutral colors in components."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#static-prototype-surfaces","title":"Static prototype surfaces","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, source buttons, and tabs are static. When implementing them, add an explicit state/data owner an","content":"Static prototype surfaces Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, source buttons, and tabs are static. When implementing them, add an explicit state/data owner and update this documentation; avoid placing navigation or persistence side effects directly inside presentational components."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html","title":"Testing & quality","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Know what the automated suite protects, where browser checks are required, and what to run before handoff.","content":"Testing and quality Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions. - src/test/setup.ts cleans up rendered React trees after every test. Tests are colocated with source files and use .test.ts or .test.tsx. Commands npm run build is also the authoritative type check because it runs tsc -b before Vite. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases. Current automated coverage The suite currently contains 29 tests across nine files. File What it protects --- --- suggestions/inbox.test.ts Dedupe, 30-item eviction, stale/withdrawn previews, frozen pins, workspace transitions, preview resolution, and z-order. suggestions/mockSuggestionFeed.test.ts Manual channel delivery, malformed-message rejection, no-op generation paths, and unsubscribe cleanup. dev/mockSuggestions/mockSuggestionDraft.test.ts Common metadata, every kind-specific payload, recursive node JSON, and validation failures. dev/mockSuggestions/MockSuggestionC"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#test-stack","title":"Test stack","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event dr","content":"Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#commands","title":"Commands","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type check because it runs tsc -b before Vite. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallo","content":"Commands npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type check because it runs tsc -b before Vite. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#current-automated-coverage","title":"Current automated coverage","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The suite currently contains 29 tests across nine files.","content":"Current automated coverage The suite currently contains 29 tests across nine files."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#why-reducer-tests-matter-most","title":"Why reducer tests matter most","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin wi","content":"Why reducer tests matter most The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin with a reducer case. Component tests should then verify that the correct intent is exposed to users."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#feed-lifecycle-tests","title":"Feed lifecycle tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The mock feed owns a browser channel while it has subscribers. Always unsubscribe and verify no new events arrive; feed cleanup is required for React StrictMode and future reconnection logic.","content":"Feed lifecycle tests The mock feed owns a browser channel while it has subscribers. Always unsubscribe and verify no new events arrive; feed cleanup is required for React StrictMode and future reconnection logic."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#geometry-tests","title":"Geometry tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace browser testing for actual scroll, res","content":"Geometry tests jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace browser testing for actual scroll, resizing, and pointer behavior."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#what-is-not-covered-automatically","title":"What is not covered automatically","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - accepted-document extraction from a real BlockN","content":"What is not covered automatically The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - accepted-document extraction from a real BlockNote document; - panel drag resizing and localStorage restoration;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#manual-regression-checklist","title":"Manual regression checklist","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"","content":"Manual regression checklist "},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#editor-and-context","title":"Editor and context","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing accepted text does not create a suggestion in manual mock mode. - Editing a temporary preview does not itself enter accepted agent context. - Block formatting","content":"Editor and context - The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing accepted text does not create a suggestion in manual mock mode. - Editing a temporary preview does not itself enter accepted agent context. - Block formatting, selection, slash menu, and normal BlockNote editing still work."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#suggestion-lifecycle","title":"Suggestion lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - Sending a direction clears the form but produces no suggestion in ma","content":"Suggestion lifecycle - The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - Sending a direction clears the form but produces no suggestion in manual mock mode. - Selecting marks an item read; Back returns to the correct queue."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#preview-lifecycle","title":"Preview lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes","content":"Preview lifecycle - Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes the block and keeps a normal source suggestion."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#desktop-layout-80rem","title":"Desktop layout ( =80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - C","content":"Desktop layout ( =80rem) - Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - Cards move, resize, stack, clamp, scroll internally, and return to Pins."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#below-desktop-80rem","title":"Below desktop (<80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable","content":"Below desktop (<80rem) - Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable and no workspace card is shown."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#accessibility","title":"Accessibility","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as te","content":"Accessibility - Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as text, not color alone. - Force invalid Mermaid source and confirm the description remains available."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#adding-tests","title":"Adding tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - document serialization: add","content":"Adding tests Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - document serialization: add focused tests for getAcceptedDocumentBlocks;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#pre-handoff-standard","title":"Pre-handoff standard","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, comman","content":"Pre-handoff standard Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, command, breakpoint, persistence rule, or static/functional boundary changed."},{"page":"extension-guide.html","title":"Extension guide","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Use the existing seams to add a real agent, persistence, suggestion kinds, editor blocks, and application actions.","content":"Extension guide This guide identifies the existing seams for likely next steps. It does not prescribe a backend or product architecture that is not present in the repository. Replace the mock writing partner Implement the existing SuggestionFeed contract and keep transport details behind it. A production adapter must define: - how it starts and stops when subscribers come and go; - how server messages map to every SuggestionEvent variant; - stable id and dedupeKey rules; - reconnection and replay semantics; - ordering of status, suggestion, and error events; - cancellation or ownership of in-flight steering calls; - what retry() retries; - cleanup under React StrictMode. Then replace createMockSuggestionFeed(contextSource) in App.tsx with the new adapter. Preserve stable construction with useMemo or move service creation above React if it is intentionally process-wide. Do not call an HTTP or model SDK directly from SuggestionDock. That would couple view lifecycle to transport lifecycle, make replay/dedupe inconsistent, and bypass reducer tests. Context sent to a real service The existing DocumentSnapshot is deliberately small. Before making it a network payload, decide and document"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#replace-the-mock-writing-partner","title":"Replace the mock writing partner","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Implement the existing SuggestionFeed contract and keep transport details behind it. A production adapter must define: - how it starts and stops when subscribers come and go; - how server messages map to every Suggestion","content":"Replace the mock writing partner Implement the existing SuggestionFeed contract and keep transport details behind it. A production adapter must define: - how it starts and stops when subscribers come and go; - how server messages map to every SuggestionEvent variant; - stable id and dedupeKey rules;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#context-sent-to-a-real-service","title":"Context sent to a real service","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The existing DocumentSnapshot is deliberately small. Before making it a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hierarchy, current selection, titl","content":"Context sent to a real service The existing DocumentSnapshot is deliberately small. Before making it a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hierarchy, current selection, title, and metadata are required;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-persistence","title":"Add persistence","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"There are three distinct data classes; do not persist the entire React/reducer state as one opaque blob.","content":"Add persistence There are three distinct data classes; do not persist the entire React/reducer state as one opaque blob."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#document-data","title":"Document data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Persist BlockNote's serializable document model and document metadata. Decide when autosave occurs and how loading replaces the initial seeded content. Handle schema versions because the custom block set may evolve. Temp","content":"Document data Persist BlockNote's serializable document model and document metadata. Decide when autosave occurs and how loading replaces the initial seeded content. Handle schema versions because the custom block set may evolve. Temporary suggestionPreview blocks need an explicit product decision on reload. The safest default is to exclude them from saved accepted content or persist them as recoverable drafts with clearly separate semantics."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#suggestion-data","title":"Suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Decide whether the live inbox is a session stream, durable server inbox, or client cache. The current seenKeys behavior means a dismissed item cannot be re-added during the page session; durable dedupe will need a delibe","content":"Suggestion data Decide whether the live inbox is a session stream, durable server inbox, or client cache. The current seenKeys behavior means a dismissed item cannot be re-added during the page session; durable dedupe will need a deliberate retention policy."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#workspace-preferences","title":"Workspace preferences","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Column widths can remain local preferences. Workspace-card geometry could be stored per document and viewport class, but restore through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add persistence thr","content":"Workspace preferences Column widths can remain local preferences. Workspace-card geometry could be stored per document and viewport class, but restore through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add persistence through a repository/storage boundary. Hydrate owners at application startup and keep serialization out of display components."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-suggestion-kind","title":"Add a suggestion kind","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SuggestionKind and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Decide whether it is text-insertable, stru","content":"Add a suggestion kind Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SuggestionKind and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Decide whether it is text-insertable, structural/reference-only, or requires a new action."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-custom-editor-block","title":"Add a custom editor block","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - age","content":"Add a custom editor block Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - agent-context inclusion or exclusion;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#implement-navigation-and-document-actions","title":"Implement navigation and document actions","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - displayed source files and Upload Sources; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and ","content":"Implement navigation and document actions The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - displayed source files and Upload Sources; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and overflow actions. Before wiring buttons individually, introduce the missing domain/state boundary:"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-artifact-upload-or-source-retrieval","title":"Add artifact upload or source retrieval","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The sidebar source list and App artifact references are currently independent mock constants. Replace them with one shared artifact owner. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact ident","content":"Add artifact upload or source retrieval The sidebar source list and App artifact references are currently independent mock constants. Replace them with one shared artifact owner. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact identity; - display metadata;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#evolve-the-inbox-reducer-safely","title":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - ac","content":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - active preview; - viewed/unread counts;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#validate-external-suggestion-data","title":"Validate external suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - tim","content":"Validate external suggestion data TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - timestamps and source-label arrays;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#introduce-routing-or-server-rendering","title":"Introduce routing or server rendering","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document q","content":"Introduce routing or server rendering The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document queries and animation frames;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#performance-watch-points","title":"Performance watch points","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - document fingerprinting serializes the full flattened snapshot on every editor change; - the context update itself is not debounced, al","content":"Performance watch points The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - document fingerprinting serializes the full flattened snapshot on every editor change; - the context update itself is not debounced, although the mock feed's observation is;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#documentation-update-triggers","title":"Documentation update triggers","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; ","content":"Documentation update triggers Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; - editor schema and accepted-context rules;"}];
